{
  "stem": "15197.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "A half an hour later, after-- or an hour later-- after Abraham was taken away, the door opened, and one of Anna Wonchalska's nephew came in and he told me, don't be afraid.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We bribed the captain from the police station.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Well, it turned out that the policeman gave my note to Anna Wonchalska.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "She knew one off our illegal meeting points.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "She went there and she started screaming, they have to do everything to take me out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And for 10,000 zlotys, it can be done because she is still in the police-- in the Polish police prison.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And they-- somehow, they get together the amount of money very fast and they bribe the captain.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And this nephew took me out from the Polish police station.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And this is how I survived and Abraham Blum was taken.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "This was one time when, really, I don't know how to thank Anna Wonchalska because she really rescued my life.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "This was a remarkable righteous person-- remarkable.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "On the Polish side, during the Uprising, we felt-- the few Jewish underground workers-- that, really, things come to an end.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "The ghetto, the hiding places will-- that maybe we will be not able, even, to survive.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "We had the list.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Nevertheless, after the Uprising, a short while later, again the underground summoned me to start looking for hiding places and to start to contact other camps.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And to do the utmost to give them-- to send them some illegal papers, some illegal identification cards.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "To rescue as many as we are able.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So mine task was not Warsaw anymore so much-- to contact other camps.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was the one who assumed new identification card.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I went to Radom camp.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I went to [NON-ENGLISH] camp.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
